text: Yeah, not really working for me. Some of these jokes are too on the nose and obvious. Oh, no one liked the Green Lantern movie so we'll make a joke about that, that's completely obvious and not done in a clever way. It doesn't even make sense. Starfire asked John Stewart if he's ever been in a movie,  to which the answer should be no, he wasn't even in the Green Lantern movie. You could have had the joke be that Hal got the role instead of John, which he's happy about because it backfired for Hal or John is jealous that Hal's more famous and popular than him. Oh, Deadpool was based off of Deathstroke so we'll make a joke about them confusing him for Deadpool. Again just a really obvious joke, not done in a clever way. When the Deadpool movie made fourth wall jokes such as Ryan Reynolds having previously played Green Lantern it was done in a clever way. I mean I saw a fan film where one of the jokes was Green Lantern confusing Captain America for "the guy that played Human Torch" and Captain America responding by confusing Green Lantern for being "the guy that played Deadpool". That's the joke. Yeah their jokes are on the level of amateurs.

text: I might not like this show but some episodes are pretty good, ok, awful , and just too awesome for words. This entire show has a bipolar personality disorder. Waffles wasn't so bad because I loved how Brother Blood kept getting pissed off. Waffles wasn't the worst but wasn't the best episode either but if you seen anything else like the episode where the Tooth Fairy wanted to replace Santa Claus now that was retarded and about the worst one and any other fart joke episode. I liked the episode: Operation: Dude Rescue. It was actually good and it seemed more on the action aspect which I respect. The Night Begins to Shine? Probably the best by far and even haters have to agree. I hate this show and I agree it's Teen Titans Go! At its best. I sometimes forgot that I'm watching Teen Titans Go! Because I don't hear a fart joke every minute or see the cheap ass animation. (I still don't know how the hell they got Ceelo Green and Fallout Boy to be in this but fucking wow). In conclusion, in a sense, I'm glad Teen Titans Go! Came on the air because it brings back nostalgia of a long lost and forgotten, once good TV show, which when this came on the air, it was given a chance at redemption for Adult Swim to continue Season 6 of Teen Titans! Hopefully now the fact it's not on Cartoon Network anymore they can do more with the characters since it's now on a more mature network. Now we can see Robin and Starfire doing it or blood, guts, horror, and violence that Teen Titans Go! Never had. To be honest I'm surprised TTG wasn't on nickjr, I mean it is just that childish.
